{"TopicId":167560,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Ross 128b, 2nd closest \u0026#039;potentially\u0026#039; habitable world","CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-15T13:08:04Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-15T13:08:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know, I know, I\u0027ve been inactive lately (but I do stalk here from time to time).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, I woke up to some pretty great news! Ross 128 has a planet!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst up, a while back, Ross 128 emitted signals (not alien), and here\u0027s the link to that\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.space.com/37579-weird-radio-signal-ross-128-star-satellite.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.space.com/37579-weird-radio-signal-ross-128-star-satellite.html\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0I also believe there\u0027s a forum thread\u00A0somewhere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut into the star! Ross 128 is a pretty calm star, with about 15% of the mass, and 20% of the radius of the Sun. It also has a much lower luminosity, meaning the habitable zone is very close in.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe planet in question has an approximate mass of 1.4x the Earth, and a possible radius of 1.2x the Earth, but until we get a direct observation, or transit, we don\u0027t know for certain.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDue to it\u0027s orbit of 9.9 days, and light flux of 1.47, it\u0027s not very certain how habitable is could be. Recent reports said an Teq of between -60c and 20c, with PHL putting it at 6.85c. It also has an ESI (Earth similarly index) of .86.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt just under 11 light years away, it\u0027s the 2nd nearest potentially habitable planet after Proxima, and likely the most promising.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome links:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://phl.upr.edu/projects/habitable-exoplanets-catalog?utm_content=buffer014e0\u0026amp;utm_medium=social\u0026amp;utm_source=twitter.com\u0026amp;utm_campaign=buffer\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://phl.upr.edu/projects/habitable-exoplanets-catalog?utm_content=buffer014e0\u0026amp;utm_medium=social\u0026amp;utm_source=twitter.com\u0026amp;utm_campaign=buffer\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.eso.org/public/news/eso1736/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.eso.org/public/news/eso1736/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.centauri-dreams.org/?p=38800\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.centauri-dreams.org/?p=38800\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThoughts? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-15T13:08:53Z\u0022 title=\u002211/15/2017 01:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 15, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-15T13:11:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m still holding out for a desert planet around Tau Ceti.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-15T13:14:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223219872\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510751480\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m still holding out for a desert planet around Tau Ceti.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh yes, I\u0027m hopeful for Tau Ceti too, it has a lot of resemblance to our inner solar system.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut Ross 128 b is probably one of our best bets for life, up there with TRAPPIST-1, I think due to the nature of the star.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-15T13:23:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223219869\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510751284\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThoughts? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s coming closer, i read ? In 79.000yr it\u0027s closer than Proxima Centauri. Proximo Ross then ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-15T13:28:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223219875\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510752228\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s coming closer, i read ? In 79.000yr it\u0027s closer than Proxima Centauri. Proximo Ross then ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, not very long at all on the cosmic scales.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ProtoJeb21","CreatedById":153551,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-15T13:53:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*overwhelming excited screaming*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-15T13:57:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223219888\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510754016\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153551\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ProtoJeb21\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, ProtoJeb21 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*overwhelming excited screaming*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat makes 6 systems within 15 light years to have possible Earthlike planets \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E I hope JWST can take a look-see\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-15T18:06:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, interesting to note, if we (for the sake of argument) had an Orion class starship, we could get to this system in ~108-110 years by flyby, double for a capture/orbit.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf we had starshot, same thing, only no slowdown. But if we used it to go to 0.15c, that would be a ~72.6 year trip, and at 0.2c which is what they want, it would take ~54.5 years to arrive.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdd on to an (Unlikely) leave time by 2030, which is what I remembered last(?), that\u0027s Ross 128b by 2084, or 2094 if we leave in 2040.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnnnnd tack on another 11 years for the signal to arrive, so between 2095 to 2105 we could have pictures from this system. Hypothetically, of course. It\u0027s just something fun to think about while I\u0027m bored. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-15T20:08:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223220087\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510769168\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, interesting to note, if we (for the sake of argument) had an Orion class starship, we could get to this system in ~108-110 years by flyby, double for a capture/orbit.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf we had starshot, same thing, only no slowdown. But if we used it to go to 0.15c, that would be a ~72.6 year trip, and at 0.2c which is what they want, it would take ~54.5 years to arrive.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAdd on to an (Unlikely) leave time by 2030, which is what I remembered last(?), that\u0027s Ross 128b by 2084, or 2094 if we leave in 2040.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnnnnd tack on another 11 years for the signal to arrive, so between 2095 to 2105 we could have pictures from this system. Hypothetically, of course. It\u0027s just something fun to think about while I\u0027m bored. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr we build giant telescopes with advanced occulters to get the pictures... we should build them in space, too...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ChrisSpace","CreatedById":140622,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-15T21:55:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223219869\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510751284\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThoughts? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s fun to think about, even if interstellar travel is a long way away.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ProtoJeb21","CreatedById":153551,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T02:44:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI made a Wikipedia page for Ross 128b!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ross_128_b\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ross_128_b\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill needs a few tweaks here and there...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoSlash27","CreatedById":111526,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T03:03:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps *technically* habitable... but only in the same sense that a dumpster fire is \u0022habitable\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry to be so dark, but nobody\u0027s going to sell their timeshare in Tahiti in order to move to the edge of a large proto- Earth tidally locked in close proximity to a red dwarf.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know I\u0027m a fun-suck,\u003Cbr\u003E\n-Slashy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T03:35:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223219875\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510752228\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s coming closer, i read ? In 79.000yr it\u0027s closer than Proxima Centauri. Proximo Ross then ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022tumblr_m78s6mEnJo1qj29hx.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022297\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_m78s6mEnJo1qj29hx.gif\u0022 width=\u0022500\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PB666","CreatedById":107380,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T04:00:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI thought that memes were banned\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223220259\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510782901\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022140622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ChrisSpace\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, ChrisSpace said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s fun to think about, even if interstellar travel is a long way away.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSend a message to the aliens of 128b and tell them to upload pictures of their planet to face-book. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T04:58:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI still wonder though, what would life adapted to lower peak spectrum/radiation looks like ? Does it look like IR camera ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ChrisSpace","CreatedById":140622,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T05:22:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223220539\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510808280\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 minutes ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI still wonder though, what would life adapted to lower peak spectrum/radiation looks like ? Does it look like IR camera ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI once read that plants around a red dwarf would be black instead of green. As for eyesight, the difference probably wouldn\u0027t be as visible as you\u0027d think.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ChrisSpace","CreatedById":140622,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T05:45:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223220453\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510800288\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153551\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ProtoJeb21\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, ProtoJeb21 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI made a Wikipedia page for Ross 128b!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ross_128_b\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ross_128_b\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill needs a few tweaks here and there...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks. So it looks like this really is the second closest potentially habitable world after Proxima. Still, at 0.1c a colony ship would take over a century to get there. Then again, Stonehenge and the GWOC both took nearly 2000 years to complete, so I guess it may be possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-16T06:00:02Z\u0022 title=\u002211/16/2017 06:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 16, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by ChrisSpace\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T15:59:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBad news about using the James Webb\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3467258157\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/PlanetQuest/status/930922594202562560\u0022 style=\u0022height:467px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre there other telescopes that could do this? What about the ELT? Or something similar? Or do we not have any telescopes that could give us more info?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T17:41:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223220794\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510847960\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBad news about using the James Webb\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5353518120\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/PlanetQuest/status/930922594202562560\u0022 style=\u0022height:424px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre there other telescopes that could do this? What about the ELT? Or something similar? Or do we not have any telescopes that could give us more info?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe this might be interesting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/XR_uEh0qhk4?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/8PstUvHlKEg?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T19:20:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/165635-nsep/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022165635\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/165635-nsep/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NSEP\u003C/a\u003E Oooooh, I\u0027ve actually been meaning to watch them, but I forgot about it \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E guess I should get on it. Thanks for the links.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T19:37:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223220924\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510860005\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/165635-nsep/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022165635\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/165635-nsep/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NSEP\u003C/a\u003E Oooooh, I\u0027ve actually been meaning to watch them, but I forgot about it \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E guess I should get on it. Thanks for the links.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo problem!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T20:30:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223220794\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510847960\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre there other telescopes that could do this? What about the ELT? Or something similar? Or do we not have any telescopes that could give us more info?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, it is possible to extract the planet\u0027s spectrum from the bright star\u0027s spectrum even if the orientation is not edge-on.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt has been done with the VLT\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.eso.org/public/archives/releases/sciencepapers/eso1002/eso1002.pdf\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.eso.org/public/archives/releases/sciencepapers/eso1002/eso1002.pdf\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand the technique can still be refined: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.eso.org/public/news/eso1517/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.eso.org/public/news/eso1517/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGMT, TMT and E-ELT could do this better (if all goes well :-)), given their shear resolution power.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce adaptive and active optics are up and running for the huge ground based telescopes, i see a future for space telescopes mainly in \u003Cem\u003Every\u003C/em\u003E large baseline interferometry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-16T20:31:38Z\u0022 title=\u002211/16/2017 08:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 16, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mitchz95","CreatedById":82292,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T20:42:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe really need more big space telescopes. Hopefully BFR or New Glenn will make that more practical.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoSlash27","CreatedById":111526,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-16T22:47:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223220841\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022167560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510854109\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NSEP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, NSEP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe this might be interesting.\u003Cbr\u003E\n*Videos featuring Fraser Cain*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI read that as \u0022Frasier Crane\u0022 and was instantly hooked on the concept \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/aNOZYL1xrGc?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022459\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Get off mah lawn!,\u003Cbr\u003E\n-Slashy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-11-16T22:51:36Z\u0022 title=\u002211/16/2017 10:51  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 16, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by GoSlash27\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}